// Page VillainOrRogue Text :
"P1611628562" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Sounds of Utter Chaos</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You hear from a communicator on the ground sounds that can only be described as utterly chaotic. You pick up the communicator and shake it a few times, trying to make out what is happening. The chaotic sounds continue, though you're able to piece together what's happening after listening to it over...and over...and over again.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>It appears that Longbow discovered an Arachnos base hidden within Founder's Falls. Whatever Arachnos was making in there prompted Longbow to send all of their forces in - including Ms. Liberty. <br><br>The raid only became worse when an explosion alerted a group of Devouring Earth, who burst into the base from underground. A group of Devouring Earth activists, hearing this, began to protest outside of the lab - believing Longbow was torturing the creatures. <br><br>The PPD showed up to try to calm the protests, however a group of Carnies attacked the police, who brought the battle into the Arachnos base. The Council, wanting to take whatever Arachnos was developing, rushed in, only for their group to be split in half by a group of sleeper agents from the 5th Column. <br><br> The battle now rages on with everyone in Founder's Falls focused on it. </scale></font></color><br> <br> ...well then. It certaintly looks like there's a good amount of action going on in Founder's Falls today."
// Answer Text :
"P1351463457" "VILLAIN: Rob a bank in Founder's Falls."
// Answer Text :
"P3223002843" "ROGUE: Wait for the battle to die down then see what it was all about."
// Page Vigilante Text :
"P1822705860" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>Sounds of Utter Chaos</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You hear from a communicator on the ground sounds that can only be described as utterly chaotic. You pick up the communicator and shake it a few times, trying to make out what is happening. The chaotic sounds continue, though you're able to piece together what's happening after listening to it over...and over...and over again.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>It appears that Longbow discovered an Arachnos base hidden within Founder's Falls. Whatever Arachnos was making in there prompted Longbow to send all of their forces in - including Ms. Liberty. <br><br>The raid only became worse when an explosion alerted a group of Devouring Earth, who burst into the base from underground. A group of Devouring Earth activists, hearing this, began to protest outside of the lab - believing Longbow was torturing the creatures. <br><br>The PPD showed up to try to calm the protests, however a group of Carnies attacked the police, who brought the battle into the Arachnos base. The Council, wanting to take whatever Arachnos was developing, rushed in, only for their group to be split in half by a group of sleeper agents from the 5th Column. <br><br> The battle now rages on with everyone in Founder's Falls focused on it. </scale></font></color><br> <br> Does anyone in Paragon even have a brain left? All of their focus is on that one battle, leaving the rest of Founder's Falls open? <br><br> This is ridiculous. Are they going to learn from their mistake? Of course not. Unless someone does something about it. Something to prove a point."
// Answer Text :
"P4079815488" "VILLAIN: Rob the bank in Founder's Falls to prove a point."
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


