// Page VillainOrRogue Text :
"P1215637028" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>8Uff00N's Left Hand</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You've found the hand of a Freakshow swiper. On the back are the words, '8Uff00N's Left Hand' - for some reason this Freakshow made it a point to label his hand. On the front is some sort of data pad, though it isn't exactly working properly. You examine the device for a few moments before causing a garbled video to play on the display. You see the fuzzy image of <color red>Doc Buzzsaw</color>.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>Hello there! If you're reading this, it means you've taken up my, Doc Buzzsaw's, offer! Or you've beaten the life out of whoever originally took up my offer. If the latter applies, then you're in luck! If the former applies, then be careful of the latter happening! But anyway let's get down to business, shall we? <br><br> I'm fascinated with the villain known as Shock Treatment and want to really get in there to study how her powers work! Unfortunately most of my boys can't get near her due to, well, the electricity she controls. <br><br> I'll pay anyone handsomely if they can bring this villain in to me! Last I heard she was going to assault a charity event Longbow was running in Nerva.</scale></font></color><br> <br> Doc Buzzsaw might not be the most stable person in the Isles, but she certainly does pay well when she puts out a job. However, one thing is a bit worrisome - the back of the datapad has a tag that reads, '2 of 4' - meaning that three other people may have gotten this message! If you're going to take up Doc Buzzsaw on her offer, you'd better act fast before someone beats you to the punch. <br><br> Although...destroying a Longbow charity event in Nerva <i>might</i> be more enjoyable than that. You might even keep Shock Treatment along to double up on the pure destruction that can be had."
// Answer Text :
"P1603280776" "VILLAIN: Destroy the Longbow charity event with Shock Treatment."
// Answer Text :
"P3016800464" "ROGUE: Stop Shock Treatment and bring her to Doc Buzzsaw."
// Page Vigilante Text :
"P2136026281" "<font face=title><scale 1.1><span align=center><color orange>8Uff00N's Left Hand</color></span></scale></font><br><span align=center><color orange><i>Alignment Mission</i></color></span><br><br>You've found the hand of a Freakshow swiper. On the back are the words, '8Uff00N's Left Hand' - for some reason this Freakshow made it a point to label his hand. On the front is some sort of data pad, though it isn't exactly working properly. You examine the device for a few moments before causing a garbled video to play on the display. You see the fuzzy image of <color red>Doc Buzzsaw</color>.<br><br><scale 1.1><font face=computer><color BurlyWood>Hello there! If you're reading this, it means you've taken up my, Doc Buzzsaw's, offer! Or you've beaten the life out of whoever originally took up my offer. If the latter applies, then you're in luck! If the former applies, then be careful of the latter happening! But anyway let's get down to business, shall we? <br><br> I'm fascinated with the villain known as Shock Treatment and want to really get in there to study how her powers work! Unfortunately most of my boys can't get near her due to, well, the electricity she controls. <br><br> I'll pay anyone handsomely if they can bring this villain in to me! Last I heard she was going to assault a charity event Longbow was running in Nerva.</scale></font></color><br> <br> You're not about to help Doc Buzzsaw move one of her plans forward - not when it's going to help the Freakshow. But one thing caught your eye - a Longbow charity event being run in Nerva. <br><br> The Rogue Isles are being run by a tyrannical organization where villain groups are allowed to run rampant...and Longbow is running a <i>charity event</i> on the island chain they have total control over? <br><br> Not making a push against Arachnos, the 5th Column, or the Council, but running a ridiculous <color red>charity event</color>? This can't stand!"
// Answer Text :
"P3907626447" "VILLAIN: Teach Longbow a lesson!"
// Page UnableToInvestigate Text :
// Answer Text :
// -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 


